Merge pull request #1 from jacobrh91/dev

Major syntax changes

Major syntax changes

To improve readability, I changed the spacing with arguments following method calls, making sure that lines are not too long.

I also changed some of the '/' symbols in some of the method calls, changing cases like "vars[X]/vars[Y]" to "strcat(vars[X], "/", vars[Y])" as I think it is more consistent and improves readability.

altered deliverables directory structure

Changed output structure so that deliverables for a particular sample go into the base delivery directory instead of their own folder within the delivery directory, as the check for "samples processing_done" requires this.

Made directory creation explicit

The workflow breaks during the GATK step if the variant folder is not explicitly created. The others were added for consistency.

Fixed error in copying of the recalibrated.bam

At the end of the workflow, sampleX.recalibrated.bam needs to be copied from its original realign location to the sampleX location within the delivery folder. However, the cp command that swift/t uses behind the scenes cannot copy a file if it needs to implicitly create a directory along the way to the file's final location.

This change explicitly creates the sampleX directory within the delivery folder
